pisode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 11\n| Title = Don't Make Me Over\n| DirectedBy = Steve Tisch \n| WrittenBy = Christopher Ames & Carolyn Shelby \n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1989|1|21}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 700070\n}}\n|}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|id=0094450|title=Dirty Dancing}}\n\n{{Dirty Dancing}}\n\n[[Category:1980s American comedy-drama television series]]\n[[Category:1988 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:1989 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television series set in the 1960s]]\n[[Category:Television series by Lionsgate Television]]\n[[Category:Live action television programs based on films]]\n[[Category:CBS original programming]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in New York (state)]]\n\n\n{{US-drama-tv-prog-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Dirty Dancing\n| image                = DirtyDancingTV88 titlescreen.jpg\n| caption              = \n| show_name_2          = \n| genre                = \n| based_on             = ''[[Dirty Dancing (film)|Dirty Dancing]]'' \n| creator              = \n| director             = \n| creative_director    = \n| developer            = Robert Rabinowitz<br>[[Barra Grant]]\n| presenter            = \n| starring             = [[Melora Hardin]]<br>[[Patrick Cassidy (actor)|Patrick Cassidy]]<br>[[Paul Feig]]<br>[[Mandy Ingber]]<br>[[Constance Marie]]<br>Charlie Stratton<br>[[John Wesley (actor)|John Wesley]]<br>[[McLean Stevenson]]\n| voices               = \n| narrated             = \n| theme_music_composer = \n| opentheme            = \"[[(I've Had) The Time of My Life]]\" by [[Bill Medley]] and [[Jennifer Warnes]]\n| endtheme             = \n| composer             = \n| country              = United States\n| language             = English\n| num_seasons          = 1\n| num_episodes         = 11\n| list_episodes        = \n| executive_producer   = \n| producer             = [[Robert Lovenheim]]<br>[[Steve Tisch]]\n| company              = [[Escape Artists|The Steve Tisch Company]]<br>[[Vestron Video|Vestron Television]]\n| supervising_producer = \n| asst_producer        = \n| co-producer          = \n| editor               = \n| story_editor         = \n| location             = \n| cinematography       = \n| camera               = \n| runtime              = 30 minutes\n| network              = [[CBS]]\n| picture_format       = \n| audio_format         = \n| first_run            = \n| first_aired          = {{start date|1988|10|29}}\n| last_aired           = {{end date|1989|1|21}}\n| related              = [[Dirty Dancing|''Dirty Dancing'' (film)]]\n| website              = \n}}\n'''''Dirty Dancing''''' was an American [[comedy-drama]] television series that ran for 11 episodes on [[CBS]] from October 29, 1988, until January 21, 1989. It was based on the film ''[[Dirty Dancing]]'' but had none of the original cast or crew. It starred [[Patrick Cassidy (actor)|Patrick Cassidy]] as Johnny ([[Patrick Swayze]]'s character in the film) and [[Melora Hardin]] as Baby ([[Jennifer Grey]]'s character in the film).\n\n==Plot==\nThe television series followed the same basic premise of the film, with a few variations. The series was still set at Kellerman's during the summer of 1963, but instead of being the daughter of a resort guest, Baby became the daughter of Max Kellerman (in the film, Baby's last name was Houseman), and was put in charge of Johnny as Kellerman's talent director. Much like the movie, Baby noted that she intended to attend [[Mount Holyoke]] in the fall, so it was not clear how the series would continue once the summer ended. As was the case in the film, Baby and Johnny had an adversarial relationship, but eventually came to respect each other. As this was a weekly series, Baby and Johnny did not fall in love immediately, but as the series progressed, their feelings grew.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Melora Hardin]] as Frances \"Baby\" Kellerman (in the film, Baby's last name is Houseman)\n* [[Patrick Cassidy (actor)|Patrick Cassidy]] as Johnny Castle\n* [[Constance Marie]] as Penny Rivera (in the film, Penny's last name is Johnson)\n* [[McLean Stevenson]] as Max Kellerman\n* Charlie Stratton as Neil Mumford (in the film, Neil's last name is Kellerman)\n* [[Paul Feig]] as Norman Bryant\n* [[John Wesley (actor)|John Wesley]] as Sweets Walker\n* Adam S. Bristol as Wallace Kahn\n* [[Mandy Ingber]] as Robin, Baby's cousin (credited as Amanda Ingber)\n\n==Episodes==\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#FFFFFF\"\n|- style=\"color:#FFFFFF\"\n! style=\"background:#700070; width:20px\"| N\u00ba\n! style=\"background:#700070\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#700070\"| Directed by\n! style=\"background:#700070\"| Written by \n! style=\"background:#700070; width:130px\"| Air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 1\n| Title = Baby, It's You\n| DirectedBy =\n| WrittenBy =\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1988|10|29}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 700070\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 2\n| Title = Heat Wave\n| DirectedBy =\n| WrittenBy =\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1988|11|5}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 700070\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 3\n| Title = Save the Last Dance for Me\n| DirectedBy =\n| WrittenBy =\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1988|11|12}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 700070\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 4\n| Title = Walk Like a Man\n| DirectedBy = [[Gabrielle Beaumont]]\n| WrittenBy = Christopher Ames & Carolyn Shelby\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1988|12|19}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 700070\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 5\n| Title = Breaking Up Is Hard to Do\n| DirectedBy =\n| WrittenBy =\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1988|12|3}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 700070\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 6\n| Title = Poetry in Motion\n| DirectedBy =\n| WrittenBy =\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1988|12|10}}\n| ShortSummary = \n